rComments: Loved her take on Canadian literature and thoroughly enjoyed her class. Definitely don't have to go to lectures but she will help you out if you do.

Attendance to lectures and tutorials isn't mandatory and there's no participation mark but there's a clear and HUGE difference if you do attend regularly. She's very caring and accessible but I found her pretty condescending when it came to dealing with admin stuff and answering questions about assignments or exams.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: An amazing professor!Helpful, intelligent, and loves what she is doing!One of the best professors at UofT so far! Also very personable and encourages students to come by office hours.

Smaro is an amazing professor; maybe it's because she's new and not yet uncaring as most UofT profs, but she's so clear and so intelligent and knowledgable. All the discussions were very relevant to current day discourse, and she genuinely wanted to hear our opinions and analyses. She's always there for you and wants you to succeed. Love!
